text:
Philippines ferry capsizes – at least 33 dead Published on : Thursday, July 2, 2015
P.C: Twitter @ANCALERTS
In a catastrophic incident in Philippines, a passenger ferry capsized with 173 passengers on board.
According to latest reports, 33 are confirmed dead while only eight bodies were retrieved. Search and rescue operations are trying to retrieve the lost bodies as soon as possible.
The passenger boat Kim Nirvana was bound for Camotes Island, Philippines and capsized off the Ormoc city pier according to the latest reports.
